Black Diamond Capital Management, L.L.C. Key Developments

Black Diamond Capital Management, L.L.C. Appoints Todd Arden as Senior Managing Director and Co-Chief Credit Officer
Jan 27 16
Black Diamond Capital Management, L.L.C. announced the appointment of Todd Arden as Senior Managing Director and Co-Chief Credit Officer. Mr. Arden will have responsibility for co-managing Black Diamond's underwriting processes and credit exposures and will also source stressed and distressed investment opportunities for Black Diamond's funds. Mr. Arden will be based in Black Diamond's Greenwich, Connecticut office. Most recently, he worked at CCMP Capital, where he served as Chief Investment Officer for Octagon Credit Opportunities, LLC. Prior to CCMP, he was a Managing Director within the distressed securities group at Angelo, Gordon & Co. In this capacity, Mr. Arden was responsible for investing in multinational corporate restructurings. During his tenure at Angelo, Gordon, he served on five company boards as the major shareholder post-restructuring.


Black Diamond Capital Management Seeks Acquisitions
Oct 7 15
Black Diamond Capital Management, L.L.C. through BDCM Opportunity Fund IV, L.P. will seek to buy middle-market U.S. and European based companies, typically through a restructuring or reorganization process. The fund has recently done successful fund raising of $1.5 million. Credit Suisse Securities (USA) LLC acted as placement agent. Roth & Zabel LLP provided legal advice.


Arclin Reportedly Engages Credit Suisse To Explore Sale
Sep 1 15
Arclin, Inc. is looking for buyers. According to sources close to the matter, the company has engaged Credit Suisse Group AG to explore a sale that could value it at around $800 million. People, seeking anonymity, added that an auction for Arclinis already under way. The news report added that spokespeople for Arclin and Credit Suisse did not immediately respond to requests for comment. Arclin is majority owned by its former creditors, Black Diamond Capital Management, L.L.C. and Silver Point Capital L.P.


